  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which are the best news website in India?",
  "response": "India has a vibrant and diverse media landscape with numerous reputable news websites catering to different regions, languages, and interests. Here are some of the best and most widely recognized news websites in India as of 2023:\n\n1. **The Times of India (TOI)**\n   - **Website:** [timesofindia.indiatimes.com](https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/)\n   - **Overview:** One of India's oldest and most widely read English-language newspapers, TOI offers comprehensive coverage of national and international news, business, entertainment, sports, and more.\n\n2. **The Hindu**\n   - **Website:** [thehindu.com](https://www.thehindu.com/)\n   - **Overview:** Known for its in-depth analysis and serious journalism, The Hindu covers a wide range of topics, including politics, technology, environment, and culture, primarily in English.\n\n3. **NDTV**\n   - **Website:** [ndtv.com](https://www.ndtv.com/)\n   - **Overview:** A leading English-language news channel's website providing real-time news updates, live TV streaming, videos, and in-depth articles on various subjects like politics, economy, and entertainment.\n\n4. **Hindustan Times (HT)**\n   - **Website:** [hindustantimes.com](https://www.hindustantimes.com/)\n   - **Overview:** A major English-language daily offering extensive coverage of national news, business, sports, technology, and lifestyle, with a focus on urban India.\n\n5. **India Today**\n   - **Website:** [indiatoday.in](https://www.indiatoday.in/)\n   - **Overview:** A prominent news magazine's online portal providing up-to-date news, features, interviews, and analysis across multiple domains including politics, entertainment, and sports.\n\n6. **Indian Express**\n   - **Website:** [indianexpress.com](https://indianexpress.com/)\n   - **Overview:** Renowned for investigative journalism and detailed reporting, the Indian Express covers a broad spectrum of news topics, including politics, business, and societal issues.\n\n7. **Scroll.in**\n   - **Website:** [scroll.in](https://scroll.in/)\n   - **Overview:** An independent digital news publication offering incisive reporting, commentary, and analysis on current affairs, culture, and technology.\n\n8. **Firstpost**\n   - **Website:** [firstpost.com](https://www.firstpost.com/)\n   - **Overview:** Provides news coverage, opinions, and analyses on politics, gaming, entertainment, and more, with a focus on engaging stories and investigative journalism.\n\n9. **BBC News India**\n   - **Website:** [bbc.com/news/world/asia/india](https://www.bbc.com/news/world/asia/india)\n   - **Overview:** The BBC's dedicated portal for Indian news offers international perspectives on events happening in India, ensuring balanced and comprehensive coverage.\n\n10. **LiveMint**\n    - **Website:** [livemint.com](https://www.livemint.com/)\n    - **Overview:** Specializes in business and financial news, providing insights, analysis, and updates on the economy, markets, and industry trends.\n\n11. **Deccan Herald**\n    - **Website:** [deccanherald.com](https://www.deccanherald.com/)\n    - **Overview:** An English-language newspaper with a strong presence in South India, offering regional and national news, along with coverage of various other topics.\n\n12. **Rajya Sabha TV and Lok Sabha TV**\n    - **Websites:** [rshtv.nic.in](https://rshtv.nic.in/) | [loksabhatv.nic.in](https://loksabhatv.nic.in/)\n    - **Overview:** Official channels providing live streams and recordings of parliamentary proceedings, debates, and discussions, offering insights into India's legislative process.\n\n**Additional Considerations:**\n\n- **Language Diversity:** India is a multilingual country with major news outlets available in various languages like Hindi (e.g., Dainik Bhaskar, Amar Ujala), regional languages, and others, catering to different linguistic audiences.\n  \n- **Fact-Checking and Credibility:** While the above-listed websites are reputable, it's always advisable to cross-verify news from multiple sources to ensure accuracy and avoid misinformation.\n\n- **Digital-Only Outlets:** Platforms like **The Wire** and **Boom** have emerged as influential digital-only news outlets, offering alternative perspectives and investigative journalism.\n\nChoosing the \"best\" news website can depend on your specific interests, preferred language, and the type of coverage you seek. Exploring a combination of these sources can provide a well-rounded view of events and developments in India and globally.",
